parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy with excessive force, causing harm to occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates and remains illuminated
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag deploys with excessive force
the passenger's side airbag sensor light remains illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to continued risk of injury or death due to the defective airbag, as well as inconvenience and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: The part to repair the airbag is unavailable
the manufacturer exceeds a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair
the vehicle owner is not notified of the repair status
the vehicle owner is advised not to operate the vehicle with a passenger in the front seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or experience sudden unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls

or experiences sudden unintended acceleration; the engine warning indicator illuminates; the speedometer reads incorrectly; smoke emits from under the hood; abnormal noises occur; the windshield wipers and dashboard lights malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
even when the accelerator pedal is not pressed; the vehicle continues to accelerate despite attempts to brake; the vehicle crashes into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the daytime running headlights can cause glare, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The headlights cannot be switched off until the vehicle is in park mode with the engine off; glare from reflected light causes reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The alternator fails
causing the vehicle to stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and puttering issues can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or putters while driving
often without warning; the engine may hesitate or lose power; the vehicle may stall when entering a highway or freeway; the vehicle may stall repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or putters while driving; the vehicle may lose power; the ECM may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving recall notifications and the lack of available parts can cause inconvenience and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Vehicle owners may not receive recall notifications in a timely manner; the repair process may take an extended period; vehicle owners may experience inconvenience and frustration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: These issues can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle may catch fire; the anti-freeze may leak
causing damage to the engine.
